FBIS4-62661 "drsov096_m_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-096 Daily Report 17 May 1994 Tajikistan New Peacekeeping Forces Commander Appointed New Peacekeeping Forces Commander Appointed PM1705101194 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 17 May 94 p 1 PM1705101194 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA Russian BFN [Report from roundup of reports by correspondents and ITAR-TASS: "Why Does General Need Bayan?"] [Excerpt] A new commander of the coalition peacekeeping forces has arrived in Dushanbe -- Colonel General Valeriy Patrikeyev. In his 56 years the new commander in chief has managed to graduate from two military academies and General Staff higher academy courses. In serving the fatherland, he has traveled the whole country from West to East. Before being appointed to Tajikistan for the past four years Patrikeyev has commanded the Transcaucasus Military District so that, as he says, he has peacekeeping experience. [passage omitted]
